            <ArticleTitle>Impact of Early Glycemic Control on Long-term Outcomes in Type 2 Diabetes: A Systematic Review</ArticleTitle>
            <Abstract>
                <AbstractText Label="BACKGROUND">Early intensive glycemic control in type 2 diabetes has been shown to reduce long-term complications.</AbstractText>
                <AbstractText Label="METHODS">We conducted a systematic review of randomized controlled trials comparing intensive versus standard glycemic control in newly diagnosed type 2 diabetes patients.</AbstractText>
                <AbstractText Label="RESULTS">Twelve trials involving 15,234 patients were included. Intensive control reduced HbA1c by an average of 1.2% and cardiovascular events by 18% over 10 years.</AbstractText>
                <AbstractText Label="CONCLUSIONS">Early intensive glycemic control provides durable benefits for cardiovascular and microvascular outcomes in type 2 diabetes.</AbstractText>
            </Abstract>
